      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor.",
      "rationale": "Formal use error analysis not required at MRL 2. Simulation workflow is executed by trained CFD engineers following documented standard operating procedures. Peer review of simulation setup is performed prior to production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this factor.",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty quantification not required at MRL 2. The k-omega SST turbulence model selection is justified by literature precedent for rotating blood-contacting device simulations. Model form adequacy is implicitly addressed through the output comparison factor."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs (viscosity, density, hemolysis power-law coefficients) must be sourced from peer-reviewed literature or direct measurement, with documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Blood rheology parameters sourced from Ballyk et al. (1994) and confirmed against Brookfield viscometry measurements at 37 °C. Hemolysis power-law coefficients (C=3.62e-7, α=2.416, β=0.785) from Giersiepen et al. (1990). Density set to 1056 kg/m³ from direct measurement. All inputs documented in simulation input record SIR-2025-11."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
